title: Valwood volleyball soars past Tift County
text:
Valwood volleyball soars past Tift County Staff Reports   
The Valwood volleyball team heads into October undefeated in regular-season play after traveling to Tift County to defeat the Blue Devils in straight sets, 25-12, 25-23, 25-11. 
Standouts in the match were sophomore libero Maylee McLeod with 10 digs, sophomore Ellie Stark with four digs and eight kills, and freshman Erin Moss with nine kills, five aces, and two blocks. Junior setter Ashley Manwell also contributed 19 assists and four aces. 
The Valiants, now 14-0 on the season and 7-0 in the region, travel to Tallahassee next Tuesday to take on North Florida Christian.
